{"word":"H1320 - בָּשָׂר - bâsâr - baw-sawr' - Body","slug":"H1320","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּשָׂר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâsâr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-sawr'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Body"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05E8; - ba&#x0302;s&#x0301;a&#x0302;r</b> - <i>baw-sawr'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H1319\">H1319</a>; <i>flesh</i> (from its <i>freshness</i>); by extension <i>body</i>, <i>person</i>; also (by euphemism) the <i>pudenda</i> of a man: - body, [fat, lean] flesh [-ed], kin, [man-] kind, + nakedness, self, skin."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1308\">H1308</a>, <a href=\"#/H1309\">H1309</a>, <a href=\"#/H1319\">H1319</a>"}]}